    desc: 'Master the ISO 19650 suitability code system and learn how to manage information issues — the formal process of transmitting, tracking, and resolving questions and changes on a BIM project.',
    intro: "A published drawing or model file without a suitability code is ambiguous. Is it for construction? For review only? For information? The suitability code system eliminates that ambiguity by explicitly stating the purpose for which information has been authorised. Combined with formal issue management — the structured process of transmitting and tracking information exchanges — suitability codes are the mechanism through which ISO 19650 turns information management from a technical discipline into an auditable, legally defensible process.",
